http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/andhra-pradesh/Vadde-pens-book/article14015737.ece

Farmer leader Kolli Nageswara Rao on Friday released a book penned by former Minister Vadde Sobhanadreeswara Rao on the master plan released by the APCRDA.The former Minister listed his objections and suggestions on the capital city, seed capital, and draft master plan in his book. He said that the he would submit the objections to the CRDA Commissioner. The former Minister demanded that the CRDA bring out a Telugu version of the master plan and see that it was available to every farmer. The deadline for filing objections should be extended after releasing the Telugu version, he said.CRDA urged to bring out a Telugu version of the master plan to beneft farmers